import { Autocomplete, Grid, Select, TextField, Typography } from "@mui/material";
import { useState } from "react";

const Verse = () => {
    const Books = [
            "Genesis",
            "Exodus",
            "Leviticus",
            "Numbers",
            "Deuteronomy",
            "Joshua",
            "Judges",
            "Ruth",
            "Samuel1",
            "Samuel2",
            "Kings1",
            "Kings2",
            "Chronicles1",
            "Chronicles2",
            "Ezra",
            "Nehemiah",
            "Esther",
            "Job",
            "Psalms",
            "Proverbs",
            "Ecclesiastes",
            "Song_of_solomon",
            "Isaiah",
            "Jeremiah",
            "Lamentations",
            "Ezekiel",
            "Daniel",
            "Hosea",
            "Joel",
            "Amos",
            "Obadiah",
            "Jonah",
            "Micah",
            "Nahum",
            "Habakkuk",
            "Zephaniah",
            "Haggai",
            "Zecharia",
            "Malachi",
            "Mathew",
            "Mark",
            "Luke",
            "John",
            "Acts",
            "Romans",
            "Corinthians1",
            "Corinthians2",
            "Galatians",
            "Ephesians",
            "Philippians",
            "Colossians",
            "Thessalonians1",
            "Thessalonians2",
            "Timothy1",
            "Timothy2",
            "Titus",
            "Philemon",
            "Hebrews",
            "James",
            "Peter1",
            "Peter2",
            "John1",
            "John2",
            "John3",
            "Jude",
            "Revelation"
    ];

    const [Book,setBook] = useState();

    return (
        <Grid>
            <Grid>
                <Autocomplete
                    options={Books}
                    value={Book}
                    onChange={(e, v) => {
                        setBook(v)
                        console.log(v);
                    }}
                    renderInput={(params) =>
                        <TextField
                            {...params}
                            placeholder="Enter Book"
                        />
                    }
                />
            </Grid>
        </Grid>

    )

}

export default Verse;
